parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The expansion and warping of the fuel tank can cause fuel leaks, difficulty in removing and reinstalling the tank, and potentially lead to a fire hazard.
symptoms: The fuel tank is expanding and warping
causing misaligned body panels
poor fit of the tank on the motorcycle's frame
and difficulty in removing and reinstalling the tank. In some cases
the tank is bubbling or spreading
and the fuel filler recess is showing cracks.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Tank Material Incompatibility with Ethanol
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The incompatibility of the fuel tank material with ethanol can cause the tank to expand and warp, leading to fuel leaks, difficulty in removing and reinstalling the tank, and potentially a fire hazard.
symptoms: The fuel tank is expanding and warping
causing misaligned body panels
poor fit of the tank on the motorcycle's frame
and difficulty in removing and reinstalling the tank. In some cases
the tank is bubbling or spreading
and the fuel filler recess is showing cracks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The front brake shudder/vibration can cause a momentary loss of control, increasing the risk of accidents, especially during frequent stops.
symptoms: The motorcycle's front end shakes or vibrates violently when applying the front brake
causing a loss of control
frequent shuddering or vibration during braking
especially when approaching a stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The deformation and expansion of the fuel tank can cause interference with other components, rendering the vehicle unsafe to operate, and making it difficult or impossible to perform routine maintenance.
symptoms: The fuel tank has expanded in length
the fuel tank is stuck in the frame
the fuel tank is interfering with the movement of handlebars
the fuel tank is unable to be removed for valve adjustment or other normal maintenance services.
